comments.body:
What is the difference between DNS1035 and csi driver name?

@saad-ali and I checked all the drivers listed [here](https://kubernetes-csi.github.io/docs/drivers.html), and none of them have underscores.  It's still not completely safe to tighten validation because folks could have written private csi drivers not intended for public consumption.  

Saad suggested that we just send out an email and release notes announcement that we're going to start enforcing the csi spec driver name in Kubernetes 1.14, since the requirement has already been documented in the CSI spec.  Does this sound like a reasonable exception to the tightening validation rule @thockin?

